The paper deals with the expressive power and succinctness of logics on structures of bounded tree-depth, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also involves the study of structures and their properties, which is related to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of quantifier alternations and modulo-counting quantifiers suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC). The study of order-invariant sentences and their translations may also be relevant to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the analysis of the expressive power and succinctness of different logics may have implications for machine learning and artificial intelligence, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
